<h3 id="data">DATA</h3>
<h4 id="1-what-am-i-predicting">1) What am I predicting</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Predict whether a given tweet is about a real diaster or not. If so, predict a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">1</code>, If not, predict a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">0</code>.</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="2-columns">2) Columns</h4>
<ul>
  <li>id - a unique identifier for each tweet</li>
  <li>text - the text of the tweet</li>
  <li>location - the location the tweet was sent from (may be blank)</li>
  <li>keyword - a particular keyword from the tweet (may be blank)</li>
  <li>target - in train.csv only, this denotes whether a tweet is about a real disaster (1) or not (0)</li>
</ul>

